my question is basically around like, you know, a lot of folks who get into data science are

00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:52.640
like really eager to use kind of new tools, machine learning, but like, and I expect this

00:18:52.640 --> 00:18:56.400
to happen in industry too, but particularly in government, there's only, we get kind of

00:18:56.400 --> 00:19:00.400
constrained about like what we can actually use. It has to be either sanctioned by IT

00:19:01.359 --> 00:19:06.000
or at least needs to meet certain guidelines and parameters, and not everyone knows how to use

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:12.959
those tools, so how do you manage kind of those expectations for folks about, you know, yeah,

00:19:12.959 --> 00:19:18.959
that looks like a great tool, but like these three things over here are the ones that our company

00:19:18.959 --> 00:19:24.959
uses or that the government uses to get our work done. Do you run into those kind of frustrations,

00:19:24.959 --> 00:19:35.680
or yeah, how do you manage that? Yeah, so there are like different reasons why that will happen,

00:19:35.680 --> 00:19:44.239
so the first one is just budget, so if they already have a license, let's say that they

00:19:44.239 --> 00:19:50.959
have a Tableau license, but we see that we could do it with Power BI because they use SharePoint,

00:19:50.959 --> 00:19:57.839
for example, but then it's like they don't have that license, and it's just budget, and to

00:19:58.640 --> 00:20:08.000
get approval for tools, and yeah, money can take time, so that's something that we need to adapt,

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:15.280
like that's the tool that they have, and if we see that we can get the approval within time,

00:20:15.280 --> 00:20:21.599
we will take the risk. Otherwise, we just go with the tools that they have approved,

00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:31.520
approved, and yeah, just work around that, and another part is what you were mentioning,

00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:38.400
that they already have some tools that they know, and they are used to that, and it's hard to make

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:46.560
them make the move. Maybe some people really want to change, but they know that some users

00:20:46.560 --> 00:20:55.439
will have some resistance to do that change, and not everybody is on the technology

00:20:57.520 --> 00:21:04.880
side. They are not very tech savvy, so we need to understand that part as well, that they have

00:21:04.880 --> 00:21:10.160
a job that is not related with technology, so it's going to be hard to move

00:21:11.119 --> 00:21:18.959
a whole group of people to go to another tool, so it depends on the audience as well,

00:21:19.680 --> 00:21:27.199
on how big of the audience it is, because one of the things that we do as well is precisely

00:21:27.199 --> 00:21:33.199
learning services, so we can prepare, or we can propose that, to prepare some

00:21:33.839 --> 00:21:42.479
trainings, some documentation that they can use, so we can use another tool, but the reason

00:21:42.479 --> 00:21:47.839
it's going to be, or it should be always, because it is cost-effective, so we are going to do it

00:21:47.839 --> 00:21:56.640
faster, or it's going to be easier to maintain. Sometimes, they are proposing things that will

00:21:56.640 --> 00:22:02.479
require a whole team on their side just to maintain that infrastructure or software,

00:22:03.439 --> 00:22:09.280
and we can propose something that is going to be just easier to maintain, and so at the end of the

00:22:09.280 --> 00:22:17.520
day, it's more cost-effective, so that's one thing, and most people will like that, so if it is going

00:22:17.520 --> 00:22:23.199
to save them time and money, they are always going to like that, but then it's the other part that

00:22:23.199 --> 00:22:29.839
they need some training or education, so that's something that we can also mitigate by providing

00:22:29.839 --> 00:22:36.800
those services as well, and there are people that are just afraid to change because

00:22:36.800 --> 00:22:43.280
they feel that it's going to take more time to change all this, and that is, at the end of the day,

