appealing to industry at the time completely changed how kind of candidates we had.

00:27:19.599 --> 00:27:26.400
That's a very good point, like hiring IT people is hard and when you are in a public sector,

00:27:26.400 --> 00:27:34.560
it's just harder for sure. I see there are a few other questions coming through on Slido as well

00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:40.319
and Yvonne, what are some of the hardest problems you find yourself trying to solve

00:27:40.319 --> 00:27:46.400
over and over again, where it feels like we don't have any good solutions available yet?

00:27:48.400 --> 00:27:50.319
Oh, that's an interesting question.

00:27:50.319 --> 00:28:06.959
I don't know, something that I've seen a lot is a lot of agencies needed that data pipeline

00:28:08.400 --> 00:28:16.719
and so they can consolidate all the information in one place and while I know that a lot of

00:28:16.719 --> 00:28:22.479
agencies have moved on to the next stage, that's something that was very repetitive

00:28:25.599 --> 00:28:32.000
and I think the challenge was exactly what we were talking about, how you can make this data

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:40.000
pipeline with those limitations. So, for example, sometimes the client doesn't want to go to the

